6,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/14\/forgive-aisha-all-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":34615,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Forgiveness: O Allah, forgive Aisha for all her sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 14, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: When I saw the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, with a cheerful face, I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, supplicate to Allah for me.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cO Allah, forgive Aisha for her past and future sins, in secret and in public.\u201d Aisha laughed so much\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25561,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/06\/adab-prophet-polite-rude-man\/","url_meta":{"origin":34615,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Adab: The Prophet is polite to a vulgar, rude man","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 6, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: A man sought permission to enter the home of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and when he saw him, the Prophet said, \u201cA wretched brother of a hostile clan, a wretched son of a hostile clan.\u201d When the man entered, the Prophet greeted him cheerfully\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7683,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/05\/prophet-wife-mood-aisha\/","url_meta":{"origin":34615,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Marriage: The Prophet can recognize his wife&#8217;s mood","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIndeed, I can tell when you are angry or pleased with me.\u201d I said, \u201cHow do you know that, O Messenger of Allah?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, when you are pleased, you say: Yes, by the Lord\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25435,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/20\/my-wife-aisha-invited-too\/","url_meta":{"origin":34615,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Marriage: Is my wife Aisha invited to dinner, too?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 20, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, had a Persian neighbour who would make good soup. He made some for the Prophet and then came to invite him. The Prophet said, \u201cAnd this is my wife, Aisha.\u201d The man said no, so the Prophet said\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/34615","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":